p4
VSarvani Sangeetha Sabha will be celebrating its 24 {+t} {+h} anniversary and conducting Tyagaraja aradhana from January 23 to 27, at Kasturi Srinivasan Hall (Music Academy mini hall), TTK Road. The series is dedicated to D. K. Pattammal.Suguna Varadachari will inaugurate the function by lighting the kuthuvilakku at 6.15 p.m. (Jan 23). A short power point presentation will be made at 6 p.m. The chief guest will be R. Vaidyanathan, GM, Indian Overseas Bank.Concerts will be held every day at 6.15 p.m., where only Tyagaraja kritis will be rendered. The artists are Dr. Pantula Rama (Jan 23 at 6.30 p.m.), B. A. Narayana and sons, Santhosh and Pavan Kumar (Jan 24), A. Kanyakumari and V. Sanjeev (Jan 25-violin duet), M.S. Sheela (Jan 26) and Malladi Suri Babu (Jan 27).Entry is free for all the concerts. For membership and other details, contact ph: 28151417.
